card count: 39/39<br />
<br />
  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Understand that I intentionally omitted obvious rares like Blade of Gondor and Lurtz from this deck. This is meant to be a deck for people without overly deep pockets, or who are just starting out. It should function well in both multi-player and two-player formats.<br />
<br />
It&#39;s a pretty straight-forward design. Using only four companions keeps the fellwship safe from nasties like Enquea, and also reduces the chance of drawing cards that you can&#39;t play. Twelve of the sixteen event-boosters work with your starting fellowship. And the Dagger Strikes aren&#39;t too difficult to pull off. <br />
<br />
The Shadow side strays a bit from the conventional cheap Moria shadow deck. That is certainly a good choice for beginners, but I thought I&#39;d try something a bit different.<br />
<br />
It&#39;s a bit more versatile, as it doesn&#39;t depend on overwhelming as does Moria. 4 Ambition and only 2 Bred For Battle cause Ambition is better: play it whenever you draw it, doesn&#39;t require exertion (big against archery) and it makes Hunt Them Down! cheaper. <br />
<br />
Goblin Runners are there in case you do need to overwhelm. <br />
<br />
Nazgul are there in a rent-a-thug role; Enquea is pretty good in any deck, and Nelya is nice versus decks sporting Thror&#39;s Map.<br />
<br />
Not really sure why Worry is in there... I think the original design called for Summit of Amon Hen in the site 9 spot, rather than Slopes of Amon Hen. It does help Enquea a bit, and could potentially punish a Prancing Pony deck that bid too high. Still, I&#39;d probably drop it, or else switch back the Summit for site 9.   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
